abstract: The three Democratic presidential candidates who got to question Attorney General William P. Barr at a Senate Judiciary Committee came away with varying levels of success.
snippet: The three Democratic presidential candidates who got to question Attorney General William P. Barr at a Senate Judiciary Committee came away with varying levels of success.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Amy Klobuchar advertised her bipartisan legislative efforts, just as she does on the Democratic presidential campaign trail. Senator Kamala Harris was prosecutorial and pointed, evoking memories of her treatment of Brett M. Kavanaugh at his Supreme Court confirmation hearing.

headline_main: Will Trump Speak at the Statue of Liberty? N.Y. Waits and Debates

abstract: As income inequality becomes a central issue for Democrats, two plans offered by Mr. Booker and Ms. Harris offer a proxy of the battle between them.
snippet: As income inequality becomes a central issue for Democrats, two plans offered by Mr. Booker and Ms. Harris offer a proxy of the battle between them.
lead_paragraph: LONDONDERRY, N.H. — On his third trip to New Hampshire recently, Senator Cory Booker had a new and very specific focus: his “baby bonds” proposal to combat income inequality by giving every child a government-funded savings account.

abstract: The Chinese telecom giant seeks acceptance in the West, but its structure and value system — patterned after China’s ruling party — could stand in the way.
snippet: The Chinese telecom giant seeks acceptance in the West, but its structure and value system — patterned after China’s ruling party — could stand in the way.
lead_paragraph: The Huawei Technologies founder Ren Zhengfei once recommended that his senior executives watch a TV series called “Proof of Identity.” In that 2009 series, a Communist spy who had infiltrated the Nationalist army during China’s civil war struggles for years to prove his loyalty and identity after the Communists prevail.

abstract: We asked you for the best advice anyone’s ever given you, and how it made an impact on your life. Here’s what you said.
snippet: We asked you for the best advice anyone’s ever given you, and how it made an impact on your life. Here’s what you said.
lead_paragraph: A few years ago, I crowdsourced an entire book, called “The World According to Twitter.” Every night for 100 nights, I tweeted a provocative question; I published the best responses. (Sample question: “Supply the subject line of an email you really, really don’t want to open.” Sample answer, from @pumpkinshirt: “To my former sexual partners, as required by law.”)
